  "text": "Kubernetes implements controller work queue with rate limiting through a comprehensive pattern located in staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/util/workqueue/. The core components are:\n\n1. **RateLimitingInterface and TypedRateLimitingInterface** (staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/util/workqueue/rate_limiting_queue.go): These define the interface for rate-limited work queues. TypedRateLimitingInterface is the generic version that extends TypedDelayingInterface with rate limiting capabilities. It provides AddRateLimited(item T), Forget(item T), and NumRequeues(item T) methods.\n\n2. **ItemExponentialFailureRateLimiter and TypedItemExponentialFailureRateLimiter** (staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/util/workqueue/default_rate_limiters.go): Implements exponential backoff based on the number of failures for a specific item. It does a simple baseDelay*2^<num-failures> limit with a configurable maxDelay. The TypedItemExponentialFailureRateLimiter uses sync.Mutex to protect a failures map that tracks retry counts per item.\n\n3. **BucketRateLimiter and TypedBucketRateLimiter** (staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/util/workqueue/default_rate_limiters.go): Adapts golang.org/x/time/rate.Limiter to the workqueue rate limiter API for overall rate limiting across all items using a token bucket algorithm.\n\n4. **Base Queue Interface with Add/Get/Done** (staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/util/workqueue/queue.go): Defines TypedInterface[T] with Add(item T), Get() (item T, shutdown bool), and Done(item T) methods. The Typed[T] struct manages a queue of items with dirty and processing sets to handle re-queueing. Add marks items for processing, Get retrieves and marks items as processing, and Done marks completion and re-adds if item was marked dirty again.\n\n5. **Controller Reconcile Loop Pattern**: Implemented across numerous controllers including staging/src/k8s.io/sample-controller/controller.go, pkg/controller/job/job_controller.go, pkg/controller/replicaset/replica_set.go, pkg/controller/bootstrap/tokencleaner.go, pkg/controller/serviceaccount/serviceaccounts_controller.go, pkg/controller/volume/pvcprotection/pvc_protection_controller.go, and staging/src/k8s.io/cloud-provider/controllers/node/node_controller.go. The pattern follows: (1) Run() starts multiple workers, (2) runWorker() continuously calls processNextWorkItem(), (3) processNextWorkItem() calls queue.Get(), executes syncHandler()/sync logic, calls queue.Done(), and on error calls queue.AddRateLimited() for retry with backoff.\n\nThe typical usage creates a rate limiter combining ItemExponentialFailureRateLimiter and BucketRateLimiter via NewTypedMaxOfRateLimiter (e.g., in sample-controller line 110-113), creates a RateLimitingInterface queue with NewTypedRateLimitingQueue, and uses a worker pattern that repeatedly calls queue.Get() to retrieve items, process them (the reconcile logic), and calls queue.Done() to mark completion. Failures trigger queue.AddRateLimited() which uses the rate limiter's When() method to calculate delay before re-queueing."
}

